7A.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*9dMAvie6c-LZ62NXS1pL7A.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*9dMAvie6c-LZ62NXS1pL7A.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*9dMAvie6c-LZ62NXS1pL7A.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:814/1*9dMAvie6c-LZ62NXS1pL7A.jpeg 814w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/max/407/1*9dMAvie6c-LZ62NXS1pL7A.jpeg"></picture></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Conversely, after your paper, the literature totally ignored your platform, like Popova et al. (29 November 2017), Ertl et al. (20 December 2017) and many others. See a <a href="https://medium.com/the-ai-lab/diversitynet-a-collaborative-benchmark-for-generative-ai-models-in-chemistry-f1b9cc669cba#c1c6" target="_self">list here</a>.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">After 4 months passed, how do you explain the persisting lack of adoption of your platform by the community ?</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In my case, I just didn’t hear about it at that time. Lack of marketing. Thanks Nathan Brown for tweeting.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">4. Your approach is too narrow, you remain within reinforcement learning models. There are important works with autoencoders, like Gomez-Bombarelli et al. (2016), Kadurin et al. (July 2017) and many others, and they deserve to be benchmarked too. Is the OpenAI gym platform restricted to Reinforcement Learning ?</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
